This article discusses a presidential memorandum issued by President Donald Trump on August 14, 2017, regarding the United States' trade relations with China. The memorandum states that the policy of the United States is to enhance economic growth, promote reciprocal treatment of American goods and investment, and strengthen the American manufacturing base. It highlights concerns about China's laws, policies, and practices that may encourage or require the transfer of American technology and intellectual property to Chinese enterprises, negatively affecting American economic interests. The memorandum directs the United States Trade Representative to determine whether to investigate China's actions that may harm American intellectual property rights, innovation, or technology development. The memorandum also includes general provisions and authorizes the publication of the memorandum in the Federal Register.